Gemini: OPEN YOUR WEB BROWSER and go to the GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE: https://console.cloud.google.com/

MAKE SURE you are in the correct PROJECT: Ensure that the project selector at the top of the Google Cloud Console is set to your ai-execution-system project.

NAVIGATE to CLOUD FUNCTIONS:

In the left-hand navigation menu (the "hamburger menu" - three horizontal lines at the top left), scroll down and find "Cloud Functions" under the "Compute" section. Click on "Cloud Functions".
FIND YOUR CLOUD FUNCTION: You should see a list of Cloud Functions. Look for the Cloud Function you just tried to deploy, which we named ai-system-backend. Click on the name ai-system-backend.

GO TO THE "LOGS" TAB: Once you are on the details page for your ai-system-backend Cloud Function, click on the "Logs" tab.

LOOK FOR "BUILD LOGS" or "BUILDS": Within the "Logs" tab, you are looking for logs related to the "BUILD" process of your Cloud Function. Google Cloud Console logs can be a bit dense. You might see different log categories or filters. Look for a filter or category related to "Builds" or "Cloud Build". Sometimes they might be directly under "Logs Explorer".

CHECK FOR ERROR MESSAGES: In the build logs, LOOK FOR ANY LINES THAT CONTAIN "ERROR" (or "Error", or "error"). These error messages will give us clues about why the build failed. Focus on errors that occurred during the "Build" phase, not just "Runtime" errors (though runtime errors are also helpful if the build succeeded but function failed at runtime later, but for now, focus on BUILD errors).

COPY AND PASTE ERROR LOGS: PLEASE COPY and PASTE any ERROR messages you find in the Cloud Function BUILD LOGS back to me. The full error message is important, not just a snippet.

EXAMPLE of what ERROR messages in the build logs might look like (this is just an example, your errors might be different):

...
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR: Could not install packages:
...
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR:   -----------------------------
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR:   Failed building wheel for openai
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR:   Running setup.py clean for openai
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR: Failed to build openai
Step #1 - "builder": ERROR:   Running setup.py install for openai ... error
...
THE CLOUD FUNCTION BUILD LOGS ARE ESSENTIAL for diagnosing this "Could not build the function" error.

PLEASE GO TO THE GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE, FIND THE BUILD LOGS for your ai-system-backend Cloud Function, LOOK FOR ERROR MESSAGES, and COPY AND PASTE THE ERROR LOGS BACK TO ME.

Let's find out why the build failed and fix it! GO! GO! GO!
